3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper introduces a new encrypted data structure called EHL and optimizes query algorithms for space and time efficiency, which are topics in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may involve some computational complexity analysis for the proposed secure sub-protocols. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve some software engineering aspects in implementing the proposed protocol and conducting experiments.
